aa(lp94
VLet me explain with a bit of amateur neuroscience.
p95
aVYour visual cortex takes up about 30 percent of your brain.
p96
aVThat's compared to approximately eight percent for touch
p97
aVand two to three percent for hearing.
p98
aVEvery second, your eyes can send your visual cortex
p99
aVas many as two billion pieces of information.
p100
aVThe rest of your body can send your brain only an additional billion.
p101
aVSo sight is one third of your brain by volume
p102
aVand can claim about two thirds of your brain's processing resources.
p103
aVIt's no surprise then
p104
aVthat the illusion of sight is so compelling.
p105
aVBut make no mistake about it: sight is an illusion.
