aa(lp107
VHere's where it gets interesting.
p108
aVTo create the experience of sight,
p109
aVyour brain references your conceptual understanding of the world,
p110
aVother knowledge, your memories, opinions, emotions, mental attention.
p111
aVAll of these things and far more are linked in your brain to your sight.
p112
aVThese linkages work both ways, and usually occur subconsciously.
p113
aVSo for example,
p114
aVwhat you see impacts how you feel,
p115
aVand the way you feel can literally change what you see.
p116
aVNumerous studies demonstrate this.
